00:01:38.866 --> 00:01:41.603 position:27% line:5% align:start
Well, look who's
here. Takemichi.

00:01:41.636 --> 00:01:44.438 position:30% line:5% align:start
You are fired.

00:01:44.471 --> 00:01:45.773 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:01:45.807 --> 00:01:47.374 position:21% line:89% align:start
Don't act surprised.

00:01:47.407 --> 00:01:50.110 position:7% line:83% align:start
You totally up and disappeared
for two straight weeks.

00:01:50.143 --> 00:01:52.279 position:16% line:83% align:start
And I'll give you just
one guess who management

00:01:52.312 --> 00:01:54.782 position:7% line:89% align:start
decided to blame for all that.

00:01:54.816 --> 00:01:55.984 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Takemichi] Wow, I'm so sorry-

00:01:56.017 --> 00:01:58.653 position:41% line:89% align:start
Fired.

00:01:58.686 --> 00:02:00.153 position:41% line:89% align:start
Right.

00:02:00.187 --> 00:02:02.356 position:16% line:83% align:start
It's been two weeks since
I went back in time,

00:02:02.389 --> 00:02:04.792 position:19% line:83% align:start
and if time passes
while I'm in the past,

00:02:04.826 --> 00:02:07.260 position:5% line:89% align:start
time passes in the present, too.

00:02:07.294 --> 00:02:09.262 position:10% line:89% align:start
Okay, what about my paycheck-

00:02:09.296 --> 00:02:11.766 position:24% line:83% align:start
[Manager] Look for
a direct deposit.

00:02:15.637 --> 00:02:17.071 position:35% line:89% align:start
Say, Naoto,

00:02:17.105 --> 00:02:19.841 position:19% line:83% align:start
I was thinking what if
I tell the past Hina

00:02:19.874 --> 00:02:21.141 position:13% line:89% align:start
what happens in her future?

00:02:21.174 --> 00:02:22.977 position:24% line:83% align:start
You know, like the
way I did with you-

00:02:23.011 --> 00:02:24.478 position:30% line:89% align:start
Absolutely not.

00:02:24.512 --> 00:02:27.682 position:13% line:83% align:start
Takemichi, are you looking
for an easy way out?

00:02:27.715 --> 00:02:29.149 position:19% line:89% align:start
No, no, it's not that!

00:02:29.182 --> 00:02:31.119 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'm not trying to
take the easy way out

00:02:31.184 --> 00:02:33.320 position:19% line:83% align:start
because life is hard
right now or anything.

00:02:33.353 --> 00:02:35.489 position:21% line:83% align:start
Plus, if you told my
sister any of this,

00:02:35.523 --> 00:02:38.358 position:10% line:83% align:start
she'd probably think you were
nuts and stop liking you.

00:02:39.727 --> 00:02:42.195 position:5% line:83% align:start
No rational person would believe
what's going on here now.

00:02:42.229 --> 00:02:43.230 position:27% line:89% align:start
How dumb are you?

00:02:44.464 --> 00:02:47.001 position:7% line:83% align:start
The only reason I believed you
was because I happened to be

00:02:47.035 --> 00:02:49.369 position:24% line:83% align:start
really into occult
stuff back then.

00:02:49.403 --> 00:02:52.272 position:10% line:83% align:start
Yeah, you were. Plus, you
were still pretty young then.

00:02:53.173 --> 00:02:54.842 position:5% line:89% align:start
Wait, did you just call me dumb?

00:02:54.876 --> 00:02:57.045 position:16% line:89% align:start
Since Sendo is dead now,

00:02:57.078 --> 00:02:59.246 position:27% line:83% align:start
we can't use him
to get to Mikey.

00:02:59.279 --> 00:03:02.249 position:16% line:83% align:start
So to save Hinata, we
have to go into the past

00:03:02.282 --> 00:03:04.418 position:13% line:89% align:start
and change Toman ourselves.

00:03:04.451 --> 00:03:06.353 position:27% line:83% align:start
So we're back to
square one again.

00:03:07.822 --> 00:03:12.160 position:19% line:83% align:start
(sighs) If only Draken
were still alive, huh?

00:03:12.192 --> 00:03:14.028 position:24% line:83% align:start
Are you talking
about Ken Ryuguji?

00:03:14.062 --> 00:03:15.262 position:41% line:89% align:start
Mm-hmm.

00:03:16.030 --> 00:03:17.464 position:21% line:89% align:start
Did you research him?

00:03:17.497 --> 00:03:18.498 position:41% line:89% align:start
I did.

00:03:20.333 --> 00:03:21.736 position:19% line:89% align:start
This is the news story.

00:03:23.538 --> 00:03:26.974 position:10% line:83% align:start
On August 3rd, 2005, in the
parking lot of Musashi Shrine

00:03:27.008 --> 00:03:28.843 position:10% line:89% align:start
in the Shibuya Ward of Tokyo,

00:03:28.876 --> 00:03:32.245 position:13% line:83% align:start
50 members of a biker gang
were involved in a brawl.

00:03:32.279 --> 00:03:34.481 position:16% line:83% align:start
A young man in his third
year of middle school

00:03:34.515 --> 00:03:36.383 position:19% line:83% align:start
was beaten and stabbed
in the abdomen.

00:03:36.818 --> 00:03:37.819 position:30% line:89% align:start
He later died.

00:03:39.419 --> 00:03:43.124 position:10% line:83% align:start
Some of these posts here
mention an internal struggle,

00:03:43.157 --> 00:03:44.525 position:19% line:89% align:start
and according to them,

00:03:44.559 --> 00:03:46.894 position:10% line:83% align:start
there was a bitter strife
between the the Mikey faction

00:03:46.928 --> 00:03:51.065 position:10% line:83% align:start
and the Draken side,
resulting in Ryuguji's death.

00:03:51.099 --> 00:03:53.167 position:16% line:89% align:start
Huh? Hey, hang on a sec!

00:03:53.201 --> 00:03:56.403 position:24% line:83% align:start
August 3rd is only
two weeks away!

00:03:56.436 --> 00:03:58.940 position:27% line:83% align:start
[Naoto] Correct,
but 12 years ago.

00:03:58.973 --> 00:04:01.109 position:27% line:83% align:start
A fight between
Mikey and Draken?

00:04:01.142 --> 00:04:02.844 position:21% line:83% align:start
There's gotta be
some kind of mistake!

00:04:04.212 --> 00:04:06.446 position:19% line:83% align:start
Draken understands
Mikey like nobody else.

00:04:06.480 --> 00:04:07.882 position:19% line:89% align:start
They're like brothers!

00:04:07.915 --> 00:04:10.918 position:13% line:83% align:start
There's no way! The idea
of them fighting is loony!

00:04:10.952 --> 00:04:12.419 position:5% line:89% align:start
So you think there's more to it?

00:04:12.452 --> 00:04:14.756 position:24% line:89% align:start
Well, I don't know.

00:04:14.789 --> 00:04:17.925 position:19% line:83% align:start
I just know Mikey could
never be Draken's enemy!

00:04:17.959 --> 00:04:21.394 position:10% line:83% align:start
Well, it is an absolute fact
that Ryuguji died that day.

00:04:22.997 --> 00:04:24.297 position:10% line:89% align:start
Let's look into it some more.

00:04:25.465 --> 00:04:29.537 position:21% line:83% align:start
Today is July 19th,
so we have two weeks.

00:04:29.570 --> 00:04:31.706 position:5% line:89% align:start
We need to find out how he died,

00:04:31.739 --> 00:04:35.042 position:24% line:83% align:start
then on August 3rd,
you'll save Ryuguji.

00:04:35.076 --> 00:04:37.477 position:7% line:89% align:start
That's your mission this time.

00:04:37.512 --> 00:04:41.281 position:7% line:83% align:start
Manjiro Sano apparently
changed after Ryuguji's death.

00:04:41.314 --> 00:04:43.217 position:27% line:83% align:start
Your friend Sendo
committed suicide

00:04:43.251 --> 00:04:45.686 position:21% line:83% align:start
because he was afraid
of Tetta Kisaki.

00:04:45.720 --> 00:04:48.022 position:16% line:83% align:start
And because Toman
became vicious and evil,

00:04:48.055 --> 00:04:49.857 position:10% line:89% align:start
they killed my sister Hinata.

00:04:52.425 --> 00:04:56.063 position:13% line:83% align:start
If you're successful, then
we can save all of them.

00:04:56.097 --> 00:05:00.300 position:7% line:89% align:start
Save Draken and Akkun and Hina?

00:05:00.333 --> 00:05:01.803 position:33% line:89% align:start
That's right.

00:05:01.836 --> 00:05:03.704 position:21% line:83% align:start
We've got the perfect
solution then.

00:05:05.907 --> 00:05:08.375 position:19% line:83% align:start
I'm going to save
Draken, no matter what!

00:05:09.177 --> 00:05:10.377 position:30% line:89% align:start
You can do it.

00:05:20.487 --> 00:05:23.825 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Takemichi] (groans)
Where, where am I?

00:05:23.858 --> 00:05:26.393 position:16% line:83% align:start
There's something on top
of me, but, what the?

00:05:32.300 --> 00:05:34.035 position:24% line:89% align:start
No kissing allowed.

00:05:35.203 --> 00:05:36.604 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:05:36.637 --> 00:05:40.041 position:7% line:89% align:start
What the hell is going on here?

00:05:40.074 --> 00:05:41.042 position:19% line:89% align:start
If there's no kissing,

00:05:42.409 --> 00:05:45.412 position:21% line:83% align:start
exactly what else
is on the menu then?

00:05:45.445 --> 00:05:47.748 position:30% line:89% align:start
(phone ringing)

00:05:47.782 --> 00:05:48.583 position:44% line:83% align:start
-Oh?
-Huh?

00:05:54.121 --> 00:05:57.357 position:10% line:89% align:start
Yeah, but add 30 minutes on.

00:05:57.390 --> 00:05:58.759 position:19% line:89% align:start
Want anything to drink?

00:06:00.061 --> 00:06:01.062 position:41% line:89% align:start
Hello?

00:06:02.063 --> 00:06:03.064 position:47% line:89% align:start
Ah!

00:06:04.332 --> 00:06:06.901 position:19% line:83% align:start
What the hell was that?
What's going on here?

00:06:09.570 --> 00:06:11.172 position:21% line:89% align:start
My past life changed!

00:06:11.205 --> 00:06:12.874 position:7% line:89% align:start
A forever-alone virgin like me

00:06:12.907 --> 00:06:15.009 position:21% line:83% align:start
somehow ended up with
that total hottie?

00:06:16.577 --> 00:06:18.713 position:13% line:83% align:start
I have to make sure Hina
never finds out about that.

00:06:18.746 --> 00:06:19.714 position:35% line:89% align:start
About what?

00:06:19.747 --> 00:06:20.548 position:47% line:89% align:start
Ah!

00:06:23.383 --> 00:06:25.353 position:16% line:83% align:start
Hinata! What in the
world are you doing here?

00:06:25.385 --> 00:06:27.387 position:19% line:83% align:start
[Hinata] I'm on my way
home from cram school,

00:06:27.420 --> 00:06:29.190 position:19% line:83% align:start
but what are you
doing here, Takemichi?

00:06:29.223 --> 00:06:31.424 position:16% line:89% align:start
Oh, uh, I was just uh...

00:06:32.793 --> 00:06:33.861 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Hinata] Hmm?

00:06:35.462 --> 00:06:39.834 position:13% line:83% align:start
Uh, what's wrong? Is there
something on my face?

00:06:39.867 --> 00:06:40.968 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Hinata] Hmm.

00:06:41.002 --> 00:06:43.470 position:21% line:89% align:start
Oh no! Don't tell me.

00:06:45.339 --> 00:06:46.774 position:19% line:89% align:start
Does she already know?

00:06:46.807 --> 00:06:50.477 position:7% line:83% align:start
Uh, I don't, uh, I don't
really remember what happened!

00:06:50.511 --> 00:06:51.746 position:13% line:89% align:start
What are you talking about?

00:06:51.779 --> 00:06:54.447 position:35% line:89% align:start
Huh? Uh...

00:06:54.481 --> 00:06:56.984 position:19% line:83% align:start
What's up with you?
You're so weird lately.

00:06:57.018 --> 00:06:58.252 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Takemichi] Huh?

00:06:58.286 --> 00:06:59.854 position:27% line:83% align:start
Today, you're the
adult Takemichi.

00:07:01.355 --> 00:07:03.024 position:21% line:83% align:start
But the night we
watched the fireworks

00:07:03.057 --> 00:07:04.491 position:16% line:89% align:start
together up on the roof,

00:07:04.525 --> 00:07:06.928 position:13% line:83% align:start
you left and just rushed
home without saying a word,

00:07:06.961 --> 00:07:08.896 position:21% line:83% align:start
and you've been cold
to me at school.

00:07:10.264 --> 00:07:11.966 position:21% line:83% align:start
But now tonight,
you seem nice again.

00:07:13.067 --> 00:07:14.368 position:16% line:89% align:start
[Takemichi] That's right.

00:07:14.402 --> 00:07:15.870 position:24% line:83% align:start
Whenever I go back
to the present,

00:07:15.903 --> 00:07:18.272 position:24% line:83% align:start
the me that's here
is the past me

00:07:18.306 --> 00:07:19.941 position:5% line:89% align:start
who has no idea what's going on.

00:07:24.278 --> 00:07:26.247 position:24% line:89% align:start
No kissing allowed.

00:07:26.280 --> 00:07:29.116 position:5% line:83% align:start
[Takemichi] How the hell did I
end up with that hottie, though?

00:07:29.150 --> 00:07:31.385 position:10% line:83% align:start
-You're such a fool, past me!
-(cell phone vibrating)

00:07:31.419 --> 00:07:33.821 position:21% line:83% align:start
Takemichi, isn't that
your phone ringing?

00:07:33.854 --> 00:07:35.656 position:38% line:89% align:start
Huh? Oh.

00:07:37.490 --> 00:07:39.160 position:24% line:89% align:start
Whoa, it's Draken.

00:07:40.194 --> 00:07:41.662 position:41% line:89% align:start
Hello?

00:07:41.696 --> 00:07:44.198 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Draken] Takemitchy, what
are you doing right now?

00:07:44.231 --> 00:07:45.700 position:5% line:89% align:start
Me? Well, I was just talking to-

00:07:45.733 --> 00:07:48.002 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Draken] Get on over
to Musashi Shrine.

00:07:48.035 --> 00:07:49.403 position:16% line:89% align:start
We're all meeting there.

00:07:49.437 --> 00:07:51.372 position:24% line:83% align:start
Huh? Um, now's not
really the best-

00:07:51.405 --> 00:07:53.841 position:24% line:83% align:start
-(line disconnects)
-Hmm?

00:07:53.874 --> 00:07:57.812 position:10% line:83% align:start
Hina, I'm sorry, but for some
reason Draken wants to see me.

00:07:57.845 --> 00:07:59.880 position:10% line:89% align:start
Fine, then I'll go with you.

00:07:59.914 --> 00:08:01.549 position:35% line:89% align:start
Seriously?

00:08:01.582 --> 00:08:03.584 position:19% line:83% align:start
Well, Draken's a friend
of yours, isn't he?

00:08:04.885 --> 00:08:07.487 position:30% line:89% align:start
(gentle music)

00:08:10.157 --> 00:08:11.491 position:24% line:89% align:start
Tell me, Takemichi.

00:08:11.525 --> 00:08:13.194 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Takemichi] Hm?

00:08:13.227 --> 00:08:14.662 position:13% line:89% align:start
What things matter to you?

00:08:14.695 --> 00:08:16.764 position:21% line:83% align:start
What do you consider
to be important?

00:08:16.797 --> 00:08:18.799 position:10% line:89% align:start
Huh? Not sure what you mean.

00:08:19.900 --> 00:08:20.701 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hmm.

00:08:22.136 --> 00:08:24.438 position:19% line:83% align:start
What's important to me
are times like this.

00:08:24.472 --> 00:08:26.841 position:10% line:89% align:start
We don't need to do anything.

00:08:26.874 --> 00:08:29.310 position:19% line:83% align:start
Just the two of us
walking along together

00:08:29.343 --> 00:08:31.278 position:21% line:83% align:start
talking about nothing
in particular.

00:08:31.312 --> 00:08:34.215 position:7% line:83% align:start
I like just being able to
relax and spend time with you.

00:08:36.050 --> 00:08:38.686 position:21% line:83% align:start
I hope we spend a lot
more time like this.

00:08:39.887 --> 00:08:43.024 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Takemichi] Time. That's
right, there's my answer!

00:08:43.057 --> 00:08:45.826 position:24% line:83% align:start
What's important to
me is saving Hina!

00:08:45.860 --> 00:08:48.696 position:7% line:83% align:start
To prevent her from getting
killed by Toman in the future!

00:08:51.832 --> 00:08:54.035 position:21% line:83% align:start
This is where you're
gonna meet him?

00:08:54.068 --> 00:08:55.136 position:33% line:89% align:start
Mm-hmm, yeah.

00:08:55.169 --> 00:08:56.704 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:08:56.737 --> 00:09:00.708 position:10% line:89% align:start
(motorcycle engine whirring)

00:09:05.246 --> 00:09:06.881 position:16% line:89% align:start
Are you sure about this?

00:09:06.914 --> 00:09:07.815 position:38% line:89% align:start
Oh, yeah!

00:09:12.853 --> 00:09:14.488 position:10% line:89% align:start
They look pretty scary to me.

00:09:14.523 --> 00:09:16.657 position:7% line:89% align:start
Yeah, but no need to be afraid.

00:09:16.690 --> 00:09:18.159 position:27% line:89% align:start
Just don't stare.

00:09:18.192 --> 00:09:19.360 position:13% line:89% align:start
They won't dare bother you

00:09:19.393 --> 00:09:21.095 position:24% line:83% align:start
if they know you're
here with me.

00:09:21.128 --> 00:09:23.532 position:21% line:83% align:start
Who wears biker gang
outfits anymore, huh?

00:09:23.564 --> 00:09:25.266 position:27% line:83% align:start
And look how many
of them there are!

00:09:25.299 --> 00:09:26.300 position:38% line:89% align:start
Hey, you!

00:09:27.201 --> 00:09:28.537 position:24% line:89% align:start
Quit your staring!

00:09:28.569 --> 00:09:30.838 position:21% line:83% align:start
What's your problem?
You wanna die?

00:09:30.871 --> 00:09:32.373 position:47% line:89% align:start
Ah!

00:09:32.406 --> 00:09:34.308 position:21% line:83% align:start
Get outta here
while you still can!

00:09:34.341 --> 00:09:35.776 position:16% line:89% align:start
While you can still walk!

00:09:35.810 --> 00:09:37.678 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'm sorry, I didn't
mean to stare!

00:09:37.711 --> 00:09:38.879 position:19% line:89% align:start
But I was invited here!

00:09:38.913 --> 00:09:42.216 position:16% line:83% align:start
Ah, bullshit! Do you
even know where you are?

00:09:42.249 --> 00:09:44.018 position:7% line:89% align:start
[Takemichi] The Musashi Shrine!

00:09:44.051 --> 00:09:46.020 position:16% line:83% align:start
Who the hell would invite
a piss ant like you

00:09:46.053 --> 00:09:47.755 position:24% line:83% align:start
to a Toman meeting,
you little bastard?

00:09:47.788 --> 00:09:49.256 position:13% line:89% align:start
[Hinata] Violence is wrong!

00:09:53.294 --> 00:09:56.063 position:7% line:89% align:start
Wait a sec, are you Takemitchy?

00:09:56.097 --> 00:09:57.231 position:30% line:89% align:start
Yeah, hi there.

00:09:58.833 --> 00:10:01.001 position:13% line:83% align:start
What are you doing scaring
the commander's guest?

00:10:01.035 --> 00:10:02.937 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Toman Member] I'm sorry
sir! I didn't know!

00:10:05.439 --> 00:10:06.941 position:27% line:83% align:start
[Hinata] Are you
okay, Takemichi?

00:10:06.974 --> 00:10:08.375 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yeah.

00:10:08.409 --> 00:10:09.544 position:33% line:89% align:start
Come with me.

00:10:09.578 --> 00:10:11.912 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Takemichi] Huh? Oh, yeah, sure.

00:10:16.183 --> 00:10:17.751 position:27% line:89% align:start
Hey, Takemitchy.

00:10:19.820 --> 00:10:22.756 position:7% line:89% align:start
Sorry, for the surprise invite.

00:10:22.790 --> 00:10:25.560 position:16% line:83% align:start
[Draken] Why'd you decide
to bring your wifey along?

00:10:25.594 --> 00:10:27.261 position:27% line:89% align:start
Sorry about that.

00:10:27.294 --> 00:10:30.131 position:16% line:83% align:start
I just had no idea it was
going to be like this.

00:10:30.164 --> 00:10:31.866 position:21% line:89% align:start
Hello again, Hinata.

00:10:31.899 --> 00:10:33.767 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'm sorry for scaring
you the other day.

00:10:33.801 --> 00:10:36.637 position:21% line:83% align:start
Oh, it's fine. That's
all forgotten now.

00:10:36.670 --> 00:10:39.240 position:21% line:83% align:start
